Do not be too hard on me, if I keep you waiting awhile with sendings for Kew; but I must first finish the “Key”;
B88.11.02. and as the last spring was a favorable one for rain towards Central Australia, I was kept also very busy to name specimens from numerous Amateur-Collectors. And now it would seem, as if we were to have 3 great exhibitions of industrial products and educts all at once in Australia!
Centennial International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1888; Centenary Universal Exhibition, Sydney, 1888; Jubilee International Exhibition, Adelaide, 1887.
